HEADWORD: Fleaking
<hw>Fleak"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A light covering of reeds, over
which the main covering is laid, in thatching houses.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Wright.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

